c‚ÄêJun Activation Protocol

Materials HeLa cells (ATCC) Formaldehyde (Sigma F1268) EMEM (BioWhittaker) containing 10% FBS (JRH Biosciences), 2 mM L‚Äêglutamine (BioWhittaker), and 10 mM HEPES (BioWhittaker) Packard 96‚Äêwell ViewPlates c‚ÄêJun Activation Hit Kit (Cellomics) Buffers and Working Solutions 1√Ç wash buffer: Add 20 ml of 10√Ç wash buffer (from Hit Kit) to 160 ml with deionized water, adjust pH to 7.2, and bring to a Ô¨Ånal volume of 200 ml. May be stored for several days at 4 . Fixation solution: In a fume hood, add 2.2 ml 37% formaldehyde to 19.8 ml 1√Ç wash buffer. Prepare fresh for each assay and warm to 37 before use. Permeabilization buffer: Add 4 ml of 10√Ç permeabilization buffer (Hit Kit) to 30 ml deionized water, adjust pH to 7.2, and bring to a Ô¨Ånal volume of 40 ml. May be stored for several days at 4 . Detergent buffer: Add 8 ml of 10√Ç detergent buffer (from Hit Kit) to 60 ml of deionized water, adjust pH to 7.2, and bring to a Ô¨Ånal volume of 80 ml. May be stored for several days at 4 . Primary antibody solution: Add 27.5 l of c‚ÄêJun primary antibody (from Hit Kit) to 5.5 ml 1√Ç wash buffer. Prepare fresh daily.

