Staining solution: Add 55 l of secondary antibody (from Hit Kit) and 2.75 l Hoechst Dye (from Hit Kit) to 5.5 ml 1√Ç wash buffer. Prepare fresh daily. Protocol 1. Culture HeLa cells to approximately 80% conÔ¨Çuency in EMEM plus 2 mM glutamine and 10% FBS. (Split 1:5 every 3 to 4 days.) 2. Harvest cells with 0.05% trypsin‚ÄêEDTA, adjust the cell number to 5 √Ç 104 cells/ml in media, and plate 100 l per well (5000 cells per well). 3. Incubate plates overnight at 37 and 5% CO2. 4. Add 20 l of medium containing 7√Ç compounds and controls in 7% DMSO. 5. Add 20 l of medium containing 5 g/ml anisomycin. 6. Incubate 30 min at 37 and 5% CO2. 7. Aspirate culture medium and add 200 l of prewarmed Ô¨Åxation solution. 8. Incubate in fume hood for 10 min at room temperature (all remaining steps are performed at room temperature). 9. Aspirate Ô¨Åxation solution and add 200 l of 1√Ç wash buffer. 10. Aspirate wash buffer and add 200 l of permeabilization buffer and incubate 90 s. 11. Aspirate permeabilization buffer and add 200 l of 1√Ç wash buffer. 12. Aspirate wash buffer, add 50 l of primary antibody solution, and incubate 1 h. 13. Aspirate primary antibody solution, add 200 l detergent buffer, and incubate 5 min. 14. Aspirate detergent buffer and add 200 l of 1√Ç wash buffer; perform procedure twice. 15. Add 50 l of staining solution and incubate 1 h. 16. Aspirate staining solution, add 200 l of detergent buffer, and incubate 5 min. 17. Aspirate detergent buffer and add 200 l of 1√Ç wash buffer; perform procedure twice. 18. Add 200 l of wash buffer, seal plates, and read on the ArrayScan.
