response. HeLa cells were plated 5.0 √Ç 103 cells per well and, after overnight culture, were treated with either 10 ng/ml OSM or 50 ng/ml PMA for 10 min at the indicated DMSO concentrations (Fig. 5D). The ERK activation response appears unaffected at DMSO concentrations 1.0%. At 5% DMSO there is an apparent increase in the Cytonuc difference for both OSM and PMA, but at 10% DMSO there are so few cells left in the wells that no values can be measured. We therefore decided that for the ERK activation assay, compounds would be diluted such that DMSO concentrations would not exceed 0.5%. Based on the results of these assay development experiments we were able to compose an ERK activation protocol.
ERK1/2 Activation Protocol

Materials HeLa cells (ATCC) Formaldehyde (Sigma F1268) DMEM (BioWhittaker) containing 10% FBS (JRH Biosciences), 2 mM L‚Äêglutamine (BioWhittaker), 10,000 units penicillin/streptomycin (BioWhittaker), and 10 mM HEPES (BioWhittaker) Dulbecco‚Äôs PBS Mg2√æ and Ca2√æ free (BioWhittaker) Packard 96‚Äêwell View Plates Phospho‚Äêp44/42 map kinase (Thr202/Try204) antibody (Cell Signaling) Alexa 488 goat anti‚Äêrabbit IgG (Molecular Probes) Hoechst 33342 (Sigma) Triton X‚Äê100 (Roche) Tween‚Äê20 (Roche) Phorbol Ester (PMA) (Sigma) Oncostatin M (OSM) (R&D) Buffers and Working Solutions Wash buffer: Dulbecco‚Äôs PBS Mg2√æ and Ca2√æ free Permeabilization buffer: PBS/Triton X‚Äê100, 0.5% Blocking Buffer: PBS/Tween 20, 0.1% Formaldehyde, 3.7%: Add 1.2 ml 37% formaldehyde to 10.8 ml wash buffer. Keep warmed to 37 until ready for use. (Prepare formaldehyde solution in a fume hood.) Primary antibody solution: 1 g/ml (Ô¨Ånal) phospho‚Äêp44/42 map kinase antibody in PBS Secondary antibody solution: 10 g/ml (Ô¨Ånal) Alexa 488 goat antirabbit IgG and 2 g/ml (Ô¨Ånal) Hoechst 33342 dye in PBS

